{
  "texts": [
    "• Provides templates for detailed audit reports (Annex I) and audit implementation reports (Annex II).This aims to ensure rigor, transparency and comparability in inaugural DSA audits.",
    "The act delineates cooperation duties between platforms and auditors, and stipulates methodologies for assessing compliance with core DSA provisions.",
    "Quantifying active users for platformsTo be mentioned as a preliminary mechanism to enact the one aforementioned, the DSA requires online platforms and search engines to count average monthly active EU users based on engagement, not just registered users or transactions.",
    "Users are considered active if exposed to content on platforms or submitting queries to search engines.The EU guidance clarifies providers should count all recipients interacting with services, including non-registered users.",
    "Mere incidental use should be excluded."
  ]
}